/-! ### Stability conditions -/

/-- A Bridgeland stability condition on a pretriangulated category `C`.
This bundles a slicing with a central charge (an additive group homomorphism
from `Kв‚Ђ C` to `в„‚`), subject to a compatibility condition relating the phase
of semistable objects to the argument of their central charge.
The slicing is required to be locally finite. -/
structure StabilityCondition where
  /-- The underlying slicing. -/
  slicing : Slicing C
  /-- The central charge, an additive group homomorphism `Kв‚Ђ C в†’+ в„‚`. -/
  Z : Kв‚Ђ C в†’+ в„‚
  /-- Compatibility: for every nonzero semistable object `E` of phase `П†`, the central charge
  `Z([E])` lies on the ray `в„ќв‚Љ В· exp(iПЂП†)` in `в„‚`. -/
  compat : в€Ђ (П† : в„ќ) (E : C), slicing.P П† E в†’ В¬IsZero E в†’
    в€ѓ (m : в„ќ), 0 < m в€§
      Z (Kв‚Ђ.of C E) = в†‘m * exp (в†‘(Real.pi * П†) * I)
  /-- The slicing is locally finite. -/
  locallyFinite : slicing.IsLocallyFinite C

/-! ### Generalized metric and seminorm -/

/-- The Bridgeland generalized metric on slicings (blueprint A8). For slicings `sв‚Ѓ` and `sв‚‚`,
this is the supremum over all nonzero objects `E` of
`max(|П†в‚ЃвЃє(E) - П†в‚‚вЃє(E)|, |П†в‚ЃвЃ»(E) - П†в‚‚вЃ»(E)|)`,
where `П†бµўВ±` are the phase bounds extracted from HN filtrations.
Values lie in `[0, в€ћ]`. -/
def slicingDist (sв‚Ѓ sв‚‚ : Slicing C) : в„ќв‰Ґ0в€ћ :=
  вЁ† (E : C) (_ : В¬IsZero E)
    (Fв‚Ѓ : HNFiltration C sв‚Ѓ.P E) (hв‚Ѓ : 0 < Fв‚Ѓ.n)
    (Fв‚‚ : HNFiltration C sв‚‚.P E) (hв‚‚ : 0 < Fв‚‚.n),
    ENNReal.ofReal (max |HNFiltration.phiPlus C Fв‚Ѓ hв‚Ѓ - HNFiltration.phiPlus C Fв‚‚ hв‚‚|
                        |HNFiltration.phiMinus C Fв‚Ѓ hв‚Ѓ - HNFiltration.phiMinus C Fв‚‚ hв‚‚|)

/-- The seminorm `вЂ–UвЂ–_Пѓ` on `Hom_в„¤(Kв‚Ђ(D), в„‚)` (blueprint A9). For a stability condition
`Пѓ = (Z, P)` and a group homomorphism `U : Kв‚Ђ(D) в†’ в„‚`, this is
`sup { |U(E)| / |Z(E)| : E is Пѓ-semistable and nonzero }`.
Values lie in `[0, в€ћ]`. -/
def stabSeminorm (Пѓ : StabilityCondition C) (U : Kв‚Ђ C в†’+ в„‚) : в„ќв‰Ґ0в€ћ :=
  вЁ† (E : C) (П† : в„ќ) (_ : Пѓ.slicing.P П† E) (_ : В¬IsZero E),
    ENNReal.ofReal (вЂ–U (Kв‚Ђ.of C E)вЂ– / вЂ–Пѓ.Z (Kв‚Ђ.of C E)вЂ–)

/-! ### Topology on Stab(D) -/

/-- The basis neighborhood `B_Оµ(Пѓ)` for the Bridgeland topology (blueprint A10).
A stability condition `П„` lies in `B_Оµ(Пѓ)` if the seminorm distance between
their central charges is less than `sin(ПЂОµ)` and the slicing distance is less
than `Оµ`. -/
def basisNhd (Пѓ : StabilityCondition C) (Оµ : в„ќ) : Set (StabilityCondition C) :=
  {П„ | stabSeminorm C Пѓ (П„.Z - Пѓ.Z) < ENNReal.ofReal (Real.sin (Real.pi * Оµ)) в€§
       slicingDist C Пѓ.slicing П„.slicing < ENNReal.ofReal Оµ}

/-- The Bridgeland topology on `Stab(D)`, generated by the basis neighborhoods
`B_Оµ(Пѓ)` for all stability conditions `Пѓ` and all `Оµ в€€ (0, 1/8)`. -/
instance StabilityCondition.topologicalSpace :
    TopologicalSpace (StabilityCondition C) :=
  TopologicalSpace.generateFrom
    {U | в€ѓ (Пѓ : StabilityCondition C) (Оµ : в„ќ), 0 < Оµ в€§ Оµ < 1 / 8 в€§
      U = basisNhd C Пѓ Оµ}

/-! ### Theorem 1.2 -/

/-- **Bridgeland's Theorem 1.2** (corrected statement). For each connected component
`ОЈ` of the topological space `Stab(D)` (with the Bridgeland topology), there exists
a linear subspace `V(ОЈ) вЉ† Hom_в„¤(Kв‚Ђ(D), в„‚)` with a topology such that the central
charge map `Пѓ в†¦ Z(Пѓ)`, restricted to the component `ОЈ` and landing in `V(ОЈ)`, is a
local homeomorphism.

This uses `IsLocalHomeomorph` from `Mathlib.Topology.IsLocalHomeomorph`, avoiding
raw `PartialHomeomorph` with `@`-threaded topologies. The statement implies that each
connected component of `Stab(D)` is a manifold locally modelled on the topological
vector space `V(ОЈ)`. -/
def bridgelandTheorem_1_2 : Prop :=
  в€Ђ (cc : ConnectedComponents (StabilityCondition C)),
    в€ѓ (V : AddSubgroup (Kв‚Ђ C в†’+ в„‚))
      (П„_V : TopologicalSpace V)
      (hZ : в€Ђ Пѓ : StabilityCondition C,
        ConnectedComponents.mk Пѓ = cc в†’ Пѓ.Z в€€ V),
      @IsLocalHomeomorph
        {Пѓ : StabilityCondition C // ConnectedComponents.mk Пѓ = cc}
        V inferInstance П„_V
        (fun вџЁПѓ, hПѓвџ© в†¦ вџЁПѓ.Z, hZ Пѓ hПѓвџ©)

